	http://www.confusedcoders.com/random/how-to-install-protocol-buffer-2-5-0-on-ubuntu-13-04

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Partial - steps:
1. Inside the extracted directory hit the below commands to install protocol buffer. These may take a while, kindly be patient.

$ sudo ./configure
$ sudo make
$ sudo make check
$ sudo make install
$ protoc --version

2. Thats it. Protocol buffer version 2.5.0 is installed on your box.

3. Note: Sometimes the latest version of protocol version does not load up. So we can do it manually by this command

$ sudo ldconfig
$ protoc --version
